<item>
            <title>[DERBY-579] Query timeout set for one statement may affect other statements with the same SQL string</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-579</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The timeout is being set on the class GenericPreparedStatement, but this&lt;br/&gt;
represents a statement plan and can be shared across multiple&lt;br/&gt;
connections (through the statement cache). Thus if two connections&lt;br/&gt;
execute the same statement with different timeouts, they will interfere&lt;br/&gt;
with each other with the timeout values.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
